<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Audacious" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Audacious,</orth> overbold, impudent: <cit><quote>saucy and a. eloquence,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 103</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 3, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.124" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.108" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 108</bibl>. Taken not exactly in a bad sense: <cit><quote>your reasons have been a. without impudency,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.5" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 5</bibl></cit> (the learned Sir Nathaniel's speech).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>